text.tspan: Share of services in total exports, 1970 to 2021
Services refer to economic output of intangible commodities that may be produced, transferred, and consumed at the same time. The share
of services in total exports comes from comparing trade in goods and services at current US dollars.
Data source: Our World in Data based on World Bank
